ghost-role-information-citadel-service-name = Citadel Resident
ghost-role-information-citadel-service-description = A resident servant of the Khs'i-Ra Empire Citadel, arrived in the sector to confirm Imperial control.
ghost-role-information-citadel-service-rules =
    You are a [color=#ff3db1][bold]Citadel resident[/bold][/color]. You are a resident servant of the Khs'i-Ra Empire Citadel, towed here 200 years ago by ADF forces to confirm Imperial control over this sector.
    However, after recently leaving your cryo-storage capsule, you noticed that the fleet that escorted you is missing, and the [color=#ff3db1]Governor[/color], ruler of the Citadel, has not yet arrived.
    After living in the sector for some time, you learned the new [color=#04bf5e]Andromeda Standard[/color] language and have a basic understanding of life in the sector.
    You are [color=red]forbidden[/color] to damage or destroy the [color=#ff3db1]Citadel[/color]. You are encouraged to keep the Citadel clean and orderly.
    The sector population may freely visit the Citadel if they do not harm or loot it.
    You are [color=red]not obligated[/color] to follow orders from the Eighth Expeditionary Fleet if they endanger the Citadel or its contents.
    Otherwise, you are free to do as you wish, including traveling across the sector, if you are confident the vault is protected.
    You [color=red]DO NOT REMEMBER[/color] your previous life or anything you learned as a ghost.
